kichta f (plural kichtas) (slang)

  1. a bundle or bysack of money or other valuables (e.g. drugs)
    • 2021 July 2, 1PLIKÉ140, “Poison”‎[1]:
      On attend juste que ton business, il évolue
      J'aime quand la kich' prend du volume, en vrai, moi, c'est tout c'que j'voulais
      We’re just waiting for your business to evolve
      I like it when the kich grows bigger, truly, me, that’s all I wanted
trans: a bundle or bysack of money or other valuables
